- Use `React.FunctionComponent` with generics in TypeScript.
- Ensure your component's props are typed using generics.
- For example, create a generic List component:
```typescript
interface ListItem<T> {
  item: T;
}

const GenericList = <T extends {}>(props: { items: T[] }) => (
  <ul>
    {props.items.map((item) => (
      <li key={JSON.stringify(item)}>{item.toString()}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
);
```
- Use `React.memo` for performance optimization with generic components.
- Ensure type safety when passing props to generic components.
- Utilize TypeScript's latest version for full compatibility and features.
